This locus is constituted by 3 subflooring support piers, in various states of preservation, laid to abut the interior face of the north wall of the Semi-circular Feature (Locus 10). Their construction style is identical to the piers described as Loci 19B and 20. The piers in this area did flank flues containing ceramic canalization tiles, as many of these sherds were found in the Locus 12 fill in the intervening bays (Locus 22).

Phase VI: Late Nabataean pre-CE 106 minor collapses and repairs. At this time the northwest subterranean channel is damaged and clogged with CE 1st c. pottery. Repairs are made to the Hexagonal Pavement as well as to the East Exedra walls. Bath Complex built.
Subflooring, abutting north wall of Locus 10.
